<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Simon: Since I got confused so bad about the level feelings I actually had them in reverse of what they are, I think we should color code them like the abilities. <p>
For example, the "you feel your luck is turning" sounds better than "you have a superb feeling" to ALL people who I've talked to whose native tongue is French from Quebec (6 people). Yet english people believed the reverse was true most of the time. 
</p>
<p>
Ideally we should have a colored word saying what the level feeling is somewhere in the left paner or status bar. 
</p>
<p>
Examples: 
</p>
<p>
Feeling: PANIC! {in red}  (as in, you're above your head in unusual things. You will probably die if you stay) 
</p>
<p>
Feeling: lucky {in green}     (risk and/or rewards! Don't tell them if it's monsters or items!) 
</p>
<p>
Feeling: hopeful {in yellow}      (some risks, some rewards, nothing really outstanding) 
</p>
<p>
Feeling: dull {in gray}                (Boring!) 
</p>
<h2 id="head-ed430a046f786f6f90fb3a3bad72b302f878c6a0"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>some chatter</h2>
<p>
Simon: The level of the character should be included in calculations, so that greater vaults of out of depth level 8 monsters in a level 2 dungeon guarding a level 3 randart would register as dull for the level 47 character who is there just because of the beastmaster. The level 1 player would however get a red feeling. 
</p>
<p>
Fates should be stated when known. I didn't pay to get my fate known just to NOT being reminded what it is when I enter the level! This prevents micromanagement and constant looking at the quest screen before using stairs...  (especially for level 1 things; sometimes I get 12 at once and one might be an artifact) 
</p>
<p>
Level feelings should UPDATE once in a while, so that when I got/killed the special stuff I know I'm done. When the preserve mode is off I *never* know for sure if the level contained *2* artifacts... 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: The colors are going to be debatable. To me, yellow is more of a "warning" color than is green. (U.S. traffic lights use red for stop, yellow for caution, and green for go.)  
</p>
<p>
I disagree with the level updating -- It makes it too easy to scum a level. (Neil convinced me.) 
</p>
<p>
Personally, I like the way Z's level feelings are done. See <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./IdeaArchive/Expand%20level%20feelings"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">here</a> for some discussion Neil and I had. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: In any case you're refering to Zangband (Z's level feelings)? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Only in part. I had another idea as well, but Neil talked me out of it. <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> Link fixed.  
</p>
